    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1869-09-03T23:55:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1869-09-02T23:56:00-05:00" n="434"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d434">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Field</persName>, Acting
                        Attorney-General, to Mr. <persName type="to">Milledge</persName>, district
                        attorney.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<date
                            ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-sibling-dates" calendar="gregorian"
                            notAfter="1869-09-03T23:59:59-04:56"
                            notBefore="1869-09-03T00:00:00-04:56" when="1869-09-03"
                        >undated</date>.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p rend="flushleft">
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">John Milledge</hi>, Esq.,<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">United States Attorney, Macon, Georgia:</hi>
                </p>
                <p>Two telegrams received. Revenue-cutters will stop all armed vessels, or vessels
                    with hostile expeditions on board, on your request. If you need a revenue-cutter
                    to cruise, make the request on the cutter and at the same time on this office by
                    telegraph.</p>
                <p>Telegraph to cutter at Apalachicola to stop expedition from Fort Gaines. Give
                    notice to such other cutters as you think best to be on the watch. If you wish
                    more authority telegraph at once.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>W. A. FIELD,<lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">Acting Attorney-General.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
